e: Belhaven omg not you,and Hell even airenwen</span><hr size=1> Verbo, <br>
<br>
I didn't attack you - I said you're learning well what the ADD leadership wants to teach you.  If you think there is something amiss in that statement, let me know where I was wrong.<br>
<br>
Your fault (and in truth that of your mates) was in engaing the mob in the first place.  If you won't let your leadership lead you into these situations, then you won't find yourself in them.  When you found another guild in Fear puling to the Shissar, you should have either offered youe help or went on your way.<br>
<br>
When ADD didn't do that - something like this is almost a foregone conclusion.  As to the ACTUAL aggro state - well, if one assumes the log's from Bippity to be accurate, then the druid had aggro and you came and took it from her.  Perhaps, because of lag from all the mobs moving around and the high population in Fear, the mob didn't appear to be moving when you whacked it to get aggro.   The point remains - you should not have been there to whack it.<br>
<br>
There are rules provided by Verant to guide folks in this situation.  They are the &quot;law&quot; in our case, and like laws, we seem to need lawyers to interpret them.<br>
<br>
To make a stark example - if a person shoots someone in the head in a public place, gets arrested and then tried, and then is acquitted because the police didn't dot every I and cross every T,   is he any less guilty of murder?<br>
<br>
You walked up and robbed Maeve.  Whether you get off remains to be seen.<br>
<br>
btw - my friendship is not blind - when someone I'm associated with begins to go down the &quot;wrong&quot; path, I'll try to pull them back.  If they persist, well, that's their path and not mine.<br>
<br>
From just under a year ago, in a post to Garaddor on your boards (dont bother to go look for it, Firius wiped it long ago)<br>
<br>
-------<br>
However, my continued presence here in your public forum is due somewhat<br>
to my sense of civic duty to those who remain in ADD (or those who<br>
joined after I left). It is akin to the responsibility one might have to<br>
direct folks around a broken bridge or away from a hazardous area. That<br>
I was never guild-bonded with somone doesn't diminish that duty. While you<br>
(obviously) do not see any need for me to perform such a service, be<br>
assured I'm not directing this information to you. <br>
-------<br>
